The paper deals with the problem of reducing the size of unrooted phylogenetic trees, which is a problem in computational biology. However, the techniques used in the paper involve graph theory and combinatorics, which are core areas of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
